      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/126/5563",
      "text": [
        " : \"أَشْهَدَ رَسُولُ اَللَّهِ صَلَّى اَللَّهُ عَلَيْهِ وَ آلِهِ عَلَى وَصِيَّتِهِ إِلَى عَلِيٍّ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ أَرْبَعَةً مِنْ عُظَمَاءِ اَلْمَلاَئِكَةِ، جَبْرَئِيلَ وَ مِيكَائِيلَ وَ إِسْرَافِيلَ وَ آخَرَ لَمْ أَحْفَظِ اِسْمَهُ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5563 - Yunus ibn Abd Al-Rahman narrated from Dawud ibn Al-Nu'man from Al-Fudayl, the servant of Abu Abdullah (as), from Abu Abdullah (as), who said:\n\"The Messenger of Allah (swt), peace and blessings be upon him and his family, had four of the great angels witness his will to Imam Ali ibn Abi Talib (as), peace be upon him: Jibril, Mika'il, Israfil, and another whose name I do not remember.\""
        ]
      }
    },
